  &lt;p style="color:#026573;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 10px 0;"&gt;Q6 — Distance de Levenshtein&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p style="color:#1e293b;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.8;margin:0;"&gt;La distance d'édition entre deux chaînes est le nombre minimal d'opérations (insertion, suppression, substitution, chacune de coût 1) pour transformer l'une en l'autre. C'est la base des correcteurs orthographiques.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p style="font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:15px;color:#1e293b;line-height:1.8;"&gt;Écrire une fonction &lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;levenshtein(X, Y)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; qui renvoie la &lt;strong&gt;distance d'édition&lt;/strong&gt; entre X et Y, via le tableau D(i, j).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style="background:#e4f1f2;border:1px solid #b7dadd;border-left:5px solid #026573;border-radius:8px;padding:14px 20px;margin:14px 0;"&gt;
&lt;pre style="color:#3b0764;font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:14px;margin:0;background:none;border:none;"&gt;levenshtein('CHIEN', 'NICHE') &amp;rarr; 4&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre style="color:#3b0764;font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:14px;margin:0;background:none;border:none;"&gt;levenshtein('chat', 'chats') &amp;rarr; 1&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</text></questiontext><generalfeedback format="html"><text /></generalfeedback><defaultgrade>2.0000000</defaultgrade><penalty>0.0000000</penalty><hidden>0</hidden><idnumber /><coderunnertype>python3</coderunnertype><prototypetype>0</prototypetype><allornothing>0</allornothing><penaltyregime>0</penaltyregime><precheck>0</precheck><hidecheck>0</hidecheck><showsource>0</showsource><answerboxlines>18</answerboxlines><answerboxcolumns>100</answerboxcolumns><answerpreload>def levenshtein(X, Y):
    n, m = len(X), len(Y)
    D = [[0] * (m + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]
    # Cas de base : transformer en/depuis la chaîne vide
    ...
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        for j in range(1, m + 1):
            # Compléter : égalité, sinon 1 + min(supp, ins, subst)
            ...
    return D[n][m]</answerpreload><globalextra /><useace /><resultcolumns /><template /><iscombinatortemplate /><allowmultiplestdins /><answer>def levenshtein(X, Y):
    n, m = len(X), len(Y)
    D = [[0] * (m + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]
    for i in range(n + 1):
        D[i][0] = i
    for j in range(m + 1):
        D[0][j] = j
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        for j in range(1, m + 1):
            if X[i-1] == Y[j-1]:
                D[i][j] = D[i-1][j-1]
            else:
                D[i][j] = 1 + min(D[i-1][j], D[i][j-1], D[i-1][j-1])
    return D[n][m]</answer><validateonsave>1</validateonsave><testsplitterre /><language /><acelang /><sandbox /><grader /><cputimelimitsecs /><memlimitmb /><sandboxparams /><templateparams /><hoisttemplateparams>1</hoisttemplateparams><extractcodefromjson>1</extractcodefromjson><templateparamslang>None</templateparamslang><templateparamsevalpertry>0</templateparamsevalpertry><templateparamsevald>{}</templateparamsevald><twigall>0</twigall><uiplugin /><uiparameters /><attachments>0</attachments><attachmentsrequired>0</attachmentsrequired><maxfilesize>10240</maxfilesize><filenamesregex /><filenamesexplain /><displayfeedback>1</displayfeedback><giveupallowed>0</giveupallowed><prototypeextra /><testcases><testcase testtype="0" useasexample="1" hiderestiffail="0" mark="1.0000000"><testcode><text>print(levenshtein('CHIEN', 'NICHE'))
